SIMPLE: training
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Training
<hw>Train"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of one who trains; the
act or process of exercising, disciplining, etc.; education.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fan training</b></col> <fld>(Hort.)</fld>, <cd>the
operation of training fruit trees, grapevines, etc., so that the
branches shall radiate from the stem like a fan.</cd> --
<col><b>Horizontal training</b></col> <fld>(Hort.)</fld>, <cd>the
operation of training fruit trees, grapevines, etc., so that the
branches shall spread out laterally in a horizontal direction.</cd> --
<col><b>Training college</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Normal school</cref>,
under <er>Normal</er>, <pos>a.</pos></cd> -- <col><b>Training
day</b></col>, <cd>a day on which a military company assembles for drill
or parade.</cd> <mark>[U. S.]</mark> -- <col><b>Training ship</b></col>,
<cd>a vessel on board of which boys are trained as
sailors.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- See <er>Education</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Training wheels</ent>⟦br⟧
